message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as summarization, question generation, and entailment generation, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of multi-task learning and neural network architectures also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of summarization and transfer learning (cs.NE) in the evaluation on the DUC-2002 dataset.
